<% layout('layouts/infoBoilerplate') -%>

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-900 to-gray-800 pt-20 pb-16 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div
            class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full opacity-10 bg-[url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/cubes.png')]">
        </div>
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-4 tracking-tight">
                <i class="fas fa-book-open text-[#fe424d] mr-3"></i> Host Resources
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Everything you need to know to become a top-rated host on
                Stayzio.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12">

            <div class="lg:w-1/4 hidden lg:block">
                <div
                    class="sticky top-28 bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-3xl p-6 shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)]">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm flex items-center gap-2">
                        <i class="fas fa-list text-[#fe424d]"></i> Contents
                    </h3>
                    <nav class="sticky-nav flex flex-col space-y-1">
                        <a href="#getting-started"
                            class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-transparent hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">Getting
                            Started</a>
                        <a href="#pricing"
                            class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-transparent hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">Pricing
                            Strategies</a>
                        <a href="#photography"
                            class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-transparent hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">Photography
                            Tips</a>
                        <a href="#guest-experience"
                            class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-transparent hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">Guest
                            Experience</a>
                    </nav>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="lg:w-3/4 prose-content bg-white p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)] border border-gray-100">

                <div id="getting-started">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-rocket"></i> Getting Started as a Host</h2>
                    <p>Welcome to the hosting community! The first step to success is creating a compelling listing that
                        accurately reflects your space.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Write a clear description:</strong> Highlight unique amenities and the local
                            neighborhood.</li>
                        <li><strong>Set your house rules:</strong> Be upfront about what is and isn't allowed to ensure
                            a good match with guests.</li>
                        <li><strong>Prepare your space:</strong> Ensure your home is clean, secure, and stocked with
                            basic essentials.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div id="pricing">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-tags"></i> Pricing Strategies</h2>
                    <p>Setting the right price is crucial for attracting guests while maximizing your earnings.</p>
                    <div class="highlight-box">
                        <h4><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Dynamic Pricing</h4>
                        <p>Consider adjusting your rates based on seasonality, local events, and weekend demand.
                            Offering weekly or monthly discounts can also help secure longer bookings.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="photography">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-camera"></i> Photography Tips</h2>
                    <p>High-quality photos are the most important factor in driving bookings. Guests want to visualize
                        themselves in your space.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use natural light whenever possible. Open all curtains and blinds.</li>
                        <li>Clean and declutter spaces before taking photos.</li>
                        <li>Capture the details: Show off unique architectural features or premium amenities like
                            espresso machines.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div id="guest-experience">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-star"></i> Creating a Great Guest Experience</h2>
                    <p>5-star reviews lead to more visibility and higher earnings. Here is how to wow your guests:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Respond to inquiries and messages quickly and
                            professionally.</li>
                        <li><strong>Welcome Guide:</strong> Leave a guidebook with instructions for appliances and
                            recommendations for local restaurants.</li>
                        <li><strong>Personal Touch:</strong> A handwritten welcome note or a small local treat can go a
                            long way.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>